A '''computerized interface scope''', was a military-grade [[Scope/Legends|scope]], mounted on a [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]]. This type of scope could interface with the wielder's helmet, allowing them to see and lock on to a target from a much farther range. An example of this type of scope would be the scope on the [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifle]] that could interface with the wielder's helmet, giving him/her an edge on the battlefield. A similar version of this device was also used on [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo's]] [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol/Legends|DL-44]] blaster pistol, allowing him to look through the scope and lock on to a target from a far-away range.

